runs.comm: good length outside off and beaten immediately, a lazy prod to a ball that cut away after pitching, misses
held it back a touch there, bowled on middle and leg, tries to turn it away towards fine leg, clips the pads
straying on the pads again, tries to glance it down fine, brushes the pads wide of a dicing Haddin towards the fine-leg boundary

good length on the off stump and angling into the right hander, tried to drive it off the front foot, missed it completely and was struck in line with middle. The umpire had no hesitation there, that looked plumb!
short of a length outside off, run down to third man
down the leg side, Haddin keeps well, diving to his left
shot! Full, overpitched outside off, McCullum gets forward and drives it confidently between point and cover for a boundary
offcutter landing on a good length outside off, Fulton is watchful early on, shoulders arms to leave it to the keeper
short of a good length outside off, good bounce there for Bracken, defended to point off the back foot
bang on target, good length on middle and leg, spat off the pitch to hit Fulton on the gloves
chases it this time, a touch fuller outside off, held its line, Fulton went for the drive but failed to make contact
drifting into the pads, tries to whip it away off his hips through square leg, hit on the thighs
full on middle and off, slower offcutter defended to cover
signs of desperation there, full outside off, walks across and tries to flick it away over midwicket, mistimes it towards cover
short of a good length on middle and off, tries to turn it away off the back foot towards square leg, gets the top edge and Haddin takes a dolly behind the wickets.
short on middle and leg, dropped into the leg side for a quick single
offcutter, good length outside off, drawing the batsman forward, defended with a closed face on the leg side
short of a length on leg stump, fends it away towards fine leg for a couple
legcutter this time and takes the batsman by surprise, good length outside off and moves away just as he tries to defend away from his body into the off side
on middle and leg, gets on the back foot and turns it away to midwicket
full on middle and off, defended off the front foot to cover, Broom is halfway down the pitch at the non-strikers end, Warner rockets in a throw but misses by a whisker. Broom was out had that hit
good length outside off, defended on the off side off the  back foot
he's bowling another superb over here, offcutter bowled on a good length outside off, opens the face to defend it to point
first run off Bracken, slower ball on middle and off, shuffles and works it away towards short fine for a single
slower ball bowled full outside off, tries to run it down to third man, misses
short of a good length outside off, pushed off the back foot to point
goes for the big one, is lucky to get a boundary, good length outside off, tries to slog that away over midwicket, gets a thick outside edge well wide of second slip
short of a length outside off, runs it down to third man for a single
short on middle and off, turned away to fine leg off the back foot
shot! Just a fraction short from Siddle, picks the length quickly, gets on the back foot and pulls it away wide of square leg for a boundary
nipped back in sharply, on middle and leg, tries to turn it away on the leg side, gets an inside edge onto his pads
decent start, good length on middle and leg, pushed off the front foot to midwicket

what a shot! Good length on middle and off, he charges down the track and slaps it between cover and point for a one bounce four. Would have been the flattest ever six had that gone over the ropes. The umpires have signaled it a six, but they will have to revisit it sometime later
clips the pads as he tries to turn that away fine
short, gets the top-edge above a leaping Haddin, tried to pull it away over square leg, gave it all and got the desired result, though the ball did'n't go in the intended direction
shot! Short and wide, just eased it past a diving point off the back foot to beat third man to the boundary
short of a good length outside off, chopped away wide of point for a single
full on the off stump, driven straight to mid-off
turned away wide of square leg for a single
good length on middle and off, defended off the back foot to mid-on
maintaining a tight line here, on the stumps, defended off the back foot to midwicket
full on the pads, flicked away to deep square leg for a single
jagged back in, tries to work it away in front of square, clips the thigh pad on the way to point
short on middle and off, pulled away in front of square, David Hussey runs a good distance from deep midwicket to cut that off just inside the ropes
short of a length on the off stump, chopped down to third man for a single
short on middle and leg, tucked away to fine leg. Fifty up for New Zealand, scored at a healthy rate
full on the off stump, driven back gently to the bowler
excellent shot! Full, overpitched outside off, makes room and drills that wide of mid-off for a boundary. Sweet sound of bat hitting ball there
slower offcutter, moved in sharply, caught Broom on the glove as he tried to run that down to third man
short of a length on middle and leg, tries to turn it away on the leg side, checks his shot at the last moment gets a leading edge into the off side
short on the off stump, comes down the track and cuts it away to third man
full outside off, gets outside the line to drive it through the off side, gets a thick inside edge wide of midwicket for a quick single
got it far more fine than he had expected, and proved extremely effective, good length outside off, tries to chop it down to third man, gets an under edge wide of the diving keeper to the boundary
short outside off, cut away well but fails to beat a diving Adam Voges at point
drilled into the ground and gets on the bounce to Voges again, good last couple of balls
tossed up on middle and leg, flicked away between deep square leg and deep midwicket for a couple
flighted outside off, reverse-swept straight to point
on middle and leg, defended off the front foot to midwicket
turned away towards a diving short fine for a single
kept low as he shaped himself for a cut, adjusted well to push it towards deep point
flighted on middle and off, tries to drive it off the front foot, gets an inside edge into the leg side for a single
full outside off, hit cleanly towards long-on where a fumble by David Hussey allows them to come back for the second
timely boundary, full outside off, sliced away over point for a crucial, pressure-relieving four
full on middle and leg, heaved away towards deep midwicket
goes for a slog over midwicket despite not being there to the pitch, gets the top-edge, Callum Ferguson runs in from deep midwicket to take a well-judged catch as it took ages to come down
guided wide of a diving point for a single
full outside off, is down the track and strokes it straight to cover on the bounce
flighted on middle and leg, turned away wide of square leg for a single
spun in sharply and missed the off stump by a whisker, short of a length outside off, tries to run that to short third, misses as it turns more than he expected, also beats the keeper
pushed off the back foot wide of cover
flat on middle and off, defended on the off side
excellent bowling here, spun in again to beat the outside edge as he tried to guide that towards point
superb over, flighted outside off, tries to reverse sweep wide of point, is hit on the pads, was struck outside the line
the runs have been hard to come by for the last couple of overs, comes down the track to push it away through the covers, is hit on the pads
tries to glance it down fine, brushes the pads, drops on the leg side and they take a quick run
full outside off, McCullum reaches for it to steer it towards deep cover
full on the pads, glanced down fine wide of fine leg for a couple
good length outside off, makes room to slice it wide of point for a couple, a wayward throw from the deep makes their job much easier
powerfully struck but straight to the fielder, short of a good length on the off stump, shuffles and pulls it away straight towards deep midwicket
he's spinning it well here, tries to counter it by dancing down the track and placing it in the leg side, struck on the pads
another dot ball, flighted outside off, tries to sweep it in front of square, hit outside the line
short and wide, goes for a sweep again, hit on the thighs
the ball spun away to beat Adam Voges at short third there, reverse swept towards him but failed to cover the spin and the ball rolls down the third-man boundary
on middle and leg, turned away behind square for a single
on leg stump, shuffles and flicks it away towards short fine for a single
a touch slower there, full outside off, cut into the batsman who went for a wild drive through the off side, was into the shot too early there, missed
moved away, short of a length outside off, tries to cut it past point, misses again
Elliot is struggling here, slightly short outside off, tries to slog it away over midwicket, misses, three dot balls
full on the off stump, struck away firmly into the deep towards the cover fielder for a single
in the blockhole outside off, dug out towards point for a single
end of an excellent over, tries to slice that away over point, fails to make contact, just two off that over
dropped, flighted on middle and off, comes down the track to loft it over the bowlers head, fails to get the elevation and Hussey puts it down while trying to pouch it over his head
tossed up outside off, reverse swept over the point fielder
pulled away straight to deep midwicket
attempts the reverse sweep again, falls just short of Adam Vpges at short fine
quicker ball on middle and leg, down the track and pushes it wide of mid-on for a single
low full toss outside off, driven wide of long-off for a couple
pulls off a Dougie Marillier shot, full toss on middle, paddles it well wide of the short-fine fielder for a boundary
good comeback, yorker fired in on leg stump, dug out wide of cover for a single
that's disappeared, length ball outside off stump, strikes it cleanly over the bowler's head and the long-off boundary, crucial hit
follows that up with a boundary, full on the leg stump, gets forward and paddles it really fine for a boundary that brings up his fifty. Excellent knock
New Zealand have come back hard in this over, just a fraction short on middle, shuffles and paddles it over the short-fine fielder for a one bounce four
eased through the coves for a single, could that be the match-turning over? 20 off it
offcutter, good length outside off, run down to third man for a single
slower ball bowled short outside off, dragged down to deep midwicket
slower ball bowled full on leg stump, flicked away to fine leg, decide against the second and wisely so, good throw into the keeper from the deep
short of a length outside off, tries to pull it away over midwicket, fails to connect, Haddin's standing up
short on the off stump, walks across and paddles it down to fine leg
fuller on the off stump, paddled uppishly towards fine leg for a single. Just five off the over

Superb catch! Could that be the decisive moment?? Full outside off, struck away straight to Voges at long-on, he takes it just inside the ropes but loses his balance, throws the ball up in the air to ensure he doesn't carry it over the boundary, trips on the way forward but retains his composure to pouch it comfortably back again, kept his cool throughout there and has possibly turned the match in Australia's favour here
full outside off, reaches for it and strokes it down to deep cover for a single
bouncer banged in short on middle, tries to upper cut that over the keeper, misses, a touch too high there and rightly given a wide
yorker on middle, dug out in the leg side for a quick single
slow full toss on the off stump, he could have smacked that anywhere but instead he gently pushes it to mid-off for a single
full outside off, chipped over the in-field wide of deep cover for a couple
swing and a miss, full outside off, held its line, tried to hit through the line and dismiss it over the long-on boundary, failed to make contact there

run out, slower offcutter bowled on a good length outside off, came forward to slog it over midwicket, runs for the single but Haddin throws down the stumps at the striker's end with an under-arm flick to find the batsman well short
full on the pads, tries to chip it away over the in-field on the leg side, is rapped on the pads and can only manage a leg bye towards cover
slower ball bowled full on middle and off, cutting away, gets down on one knee to smack it over midwicket, hit on the pads as he fails to pick the slower one, a missed opportunity there
hats off to Bracken! Short on middle and off, goes for the pull, misses yet again, Haddin prevents the single
gets a boundary, sorry but that's not quite enough!! Full on middle and leg, dragged away wide of square leg, went all along the ground there
massive six! A little too late though, short on middle and off, pulled away over the deep midwicket boundary for a big one!
